abstract: KINGSTON, N.Y., Oct. 15.--The Prohibitionists have commenced a tent campaign in this city. The canvas is stretched in a vacant lot in the business centre. abstract: HELENA, Montana, Oct. 17.--A week ago news was received from Billings that Lewis Sweet, Assessor of the county, had committed suicide. abstract: ST. LOUIS, Mo., Oct. 29.--James Ward, a trapeze performer at the London Theatre, met a frightful fate before a crowded house last night. He is 25 years  old and single.

abstract: ITHACA, N.Y., Oct. 30.--In order to check any spread of scarlet fever, which has prostrated one of the Cornell University students, the authorities have obliged six other students, who roomed in the house with the patient, to leave the city at once. Strict preventive measures are being taken to confine the disease to this one case.
